  "prompt": "What is a nomination fee?",
  "response": "A nomination fee is a charge paid by a candidate or their supporters when being considered for a specific position, award, or opportunity. The purpose can vary depending on the context:\n\n1. Political context: A fee paid to formally submit or register a candidate for an election or political position.\n\n2. Awards/Recognition: A fee required to submit a candidate for consideration in a particular award or honor.\n\n3. Sports/Organizations: Sometimes used when proposing someone for membership or a specific role within a group or organization.\n\nThe fee typically helps cover administrative costs associated with processing and reviewing nominations, and can serve as a way to demonstrate serious intent or commitment.",
